 To: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
 
 
 Hi,
 
 There is some king of misunderstanding here. Maybe I didn't provide
 clear enough explanation. Here are the steps to reproduce the problem
 and some screenshots.
 
 1) In the definition window mark code at least 2 rows long without
 using your mouse. Instead use your keyboard by holding down the shift
 key and using the up/down arrows. Start marking from top to bottom.
 See Screenshot1
 
 2) Now if you press and hold shift and press the left/right arrow, you
 will see, that you can select/deselect characters from the last marked
 row. See Screenshot 2. So the cursor is placed on the last selected
 row and if I press 'END' button it should mark the line till the end.
 This is working as expected.
 
 3) But if you try to DESELECT the last selected line to it's
 beginning, by pressing the 'HOME' button, the row on the top is marked
 to the beginning.
 
 So what I see is this: Screenshot3 (look at the top left corner in
 Scr3) but I expected this: Screenshot4 (look at the bottom left corner
 of Scr4).
 
 I hope, that this is enough as an example. If this is expected
 behaviour, please let me know, but if it's not I hope the bug will be
 easily fixed.
 
 Best regards,
 
 Lyubomir
 
