Subject: Re: Re: Re: [racket-bug] all/11768: Navigation with <shift> + Home is broken
Date: Thu, 17 Mar 2011 08:11:57 -0600

 On Thu, Mar 17, 2011 at 6:36 AM, Ll Ss <leh@abv.bg> wrote:
 > Hi,
 >
 > What I expected from the code editor is, that it should behave like any
 > other text editor - notepad, ultraEdit and so on. For example if you select
 > one row, you can deselect it by holding down shift and pressing home, and
 > again select the whole row by holding down shift and pressing end button.
 >
 > Of course the selection performed at step 3 could be changed to something
 > more "racket" specific - for example holding down shift and pressing end
 > will trigger a selection of the code between the corresponding brackets (for
 > ex. 4th opening and 4th closing bracket); or holding down shift and pressing
 > end will deselect the code between corresponding brackets. I'll leave the
 > implementation to you, as I'm sure you'll come with a good idea.
 
 Ah. Thanks for pointing me to Notepad. It looks like they have a
 different notion of the internal state relating to the shift-movement
 keys than we do. Theirs seems better, so I'll look into adjusting ours
 to match.
 
 Robby
From: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
To: bugs@racket-lang.org, Matthew Flatt <mflatt@cs.utah.edu>
Cc: 
Subject: Re: Re: Re: [racket-bug] all/11768: Navigation with <shift> + Home is broken
Date: Thu, 17 Mar 2011 08:13:01 -0600

 The different state seems to be a single position only, not a range
 with the invariant that that single position is always at one end or
 the other of the selection.  (We have, iiuc, a range that is only
 guaranteed to be inside the selection.)
 
 This affects all kinds of things like clicking and dragging, for example.
 
 Robby
